                <head>No. 386.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Comly</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Honolulu</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-06-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 8, 1880</date>. (Received June
                        24.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 111.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your No. 58, received last night, I
                    have the honor to report that, after further verbal discussion and some
                    importunity, I have a promise that all future cases analogous to that of Patrick
                    Quinn shall be disposed of in the same way with that, upon simple application
                    direct to the Hawaiian minister of finance. Accordingly I have called his
                    attention to twelve cases in which American citizens have been illegally
                    compelled to pay taxes for which thev were not liable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAMES M. COMLY.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
